Here are both approaches using Shell navigation and `IQueryAttributable`:

## 1. Register the route

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

```csharp
// ProductListViewModel.cs â€” bound to CollectionView.SelectionChangedCommand

// Approach A: string ID via query string
async Task OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}

// Approach B: full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
async Task OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

## 3. Receive data on the target ViewModel

```csharp
// ProductDetailsViewModel.cs
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    private readonly IProductService _productService;

    public ProductDetailsViewModel(IProductService productService)
    {
        _productService = productService;
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: received as a string â€” load from service
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            Product = _productService.GetProduct(id.ToString());
        }

        // Approach B: received as the actual object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
        }
    }
}
```

## Key differences

| | Query string (`?key=val`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | Strings only | Any object |
| **Deep-linkable** | âś… Yes | âťŚ No |
| **Serialization** | You handle it | None needed |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, flags | Complex/large objects |

**Tips:**
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` â€” fire-and-forget causes race conditions.
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called before the page appears, so data is ready for binding.
- You can combine both approaches in a single `ApplyQueryAttributes` method as shown aboveâ€”check whichever key is present.
